import React, { useId, useRef } from "react";

export const FlowerCartAddress = () => {
  const addressID = useId();
  const radioID = useId();
  const textReferanse = useRef(null);

  return (
    <article className="Flowers__Cart__DeliveryInfo">
      <form id="Flowers__Cart__DeliveryInfo__DeliveryAttributes">
        <label htmlFor={`${addressID}_city`}>City or suburban:</label>
        <input type="address" id={`${addressID}_city`} />
        <label htmlFor={`${addressID}_address`}>Address to deliver:</label>
        <input type="address" id={`${addressID}_address`} />
        <label htmlFor={`${addressID}_date`}>Delivery data:</label>
        <input type="date" id={`${addressID}_date`} />
        <label htmlFor={`${addressID}_time`}>Better to deliver on:</label>
        <select id={`${addressID}_time`} name="Delivery time">
          <option>12-14</option>
          <option>14-16</option>
          <option>16-18</option>
          <option>18-20</option>
          <option>20-22</option>
        </select>
        <label htmlFor={`${addressID}_comment`}>Additional comment:</label>
        <textarea ref={textReferanse} id={`${addressID}_comment`}></textarea>
      </form>
      <form id="Flowers__Cart__DeliveryInfo__DeliveryTypeRadio">
        <label>
          <input type="radio" name="type_of_order" id={`${radioID}001`} />
          Delivery
        </label>
        <label>
          <input type="radio" name="type_of_order" id={`${radioID}002`} />
          Take away
        </label>
      </form>
      <label htmlFor={`${addressID}_promocode`}>Promocode (optional):</label>
      <input type="text" id={`${addressID}_promocode`} />
    </article>
  );
};
